alert.note: Alert for Coastal Franklin; Coastal Wakulla; Inland Franklin; Inland Wakulla (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 2:20PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Wakulla, southeastern Liberty and northeastern Franklin Counties through 300 PM EDT... At 219 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7 miles north of Carrabelle, moving east at 15 mph. HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Sopchoppy, Saint Teresa, Turkey Point, Buckhorn, Panacea-Wakulla Airport, Mcintyre, Lanark Village, Sanborn, Curtis Mill, Panacea, Medart and Arran. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
